        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend Framework is great, I have only two problems with it. One is that there is no AJAX support yet, I use JQuery. Although, this gives me tight control using JQuery. The other is that the view has a lot of $this-> all throughout, I would prefer something simular to CakePHP where you have $helper-> and $view-> etc.\nThe $this-> feels very redundant to have to type everywhere and bloats my view.\nAt least in CakePHP you know your accessing a helper because you use $helper->\nI know you may feel this is not critical, its a usability problem which can make people annoyed.\nUsability can be important."
        },
