        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21917",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=philip",
                        "name": "philip",
                        "displayName": "philip",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I noticed that another programmer finds it excessive.\n\nHe was able to replace one with the other of:\n<?= @$var; ?>\nis same as\n<?php echo $this->escape($this->var); ?>\n\nhttp:\/\/akrabat.com\/2008\/02\/05\/a-view-stream-with-zend_view\/\nand\nhttp:\/\/code.google.com\/p\/simple-php-template\/\n\nMaybe you can introduce a shorthand notation?\n\nI like the CakePHP way, you get $view-> $somethingelse-> ... I know it goes against the ZF way of doing things, \"use at will\" and your keeping the namespace clean in the view, but could there be some compromise by adding a shorthand notation?\nI can do it my way, but it leads to non-standard code.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=philip",
                        "name": "philip",
                        "displayName": "philip",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-24T19:26:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-24T19:26:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21919",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Several things to note here.\n\nFirst, this past week, we announced a partnership with Dojo, and will be shipping Dojo with ZF starting with 1.6.0. Additionally, we have a variety of support for Ajax already: Json view and action helpers, the ContextSwitch and AjaxContext action helpers, the AutoComplete action helper, etc. It is incredibly trivial to utilize Ajax with ZF already.\n\nSecond, regarding removing '$this' from our View implementation: will not happen. The '$this' variable is in part an implementation detail, and would take a complete rewrite to remove. Besides that, there are _good_ reasons for retaining it: it provides a separate variable scope for variables assigned to the view, allows helpers to be encapsulated as classes and not functions (we utilize method overloading in the view object to map helpers to method calls), and provides other functionality that would be unachievable otherwise.\n\nWe do have a stream wrapper implementation available in the incubator currently, but it does not remove the $this calls; however, it can serve as a blueprint for doing so. Finally, you may always create your own view implementation by implementing Zend_View_Interface.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-25T07:14:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-25T07:14:05.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
